14 WHEREAS, Buc-ee's started in Texas and has expanded to eight other states, including
15 Georgia, and has travel centers in Warner Robins and Calhoun, one scheduled to open in
16 Brunswick in June of this year, and another planned for Monroe County; and
17 WHEREAS, each location of Buc-ee's in this state brings jobs for the development and
18 construction of the travel center; adds full-time, part-time, and seasonal jobs at the travel
19 center; increases sales tax revenue from purchases of fuel, merchandise, food, and beverages
20 at the travel center; and encourages investment in the area surrounding the travel center; and
21 WHEREAS, Georgia travelers and travelers through Georgia deserve a safe, well-lit place
22 to stop, shop, refuel, and rest, and they can happily say "Meet me at Buc-ee's!" 24 hours a
23 day, 365 days a year; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that Buc-ee's be recognized for coming to this
25 state, stimulating the economy, and providing a cultural experience to remember and revisit.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize March 20, 2025, as Buc-ee's Day at the state capitol and
28 celebrate Buc-ee's for its presence in Georgia and extend best wishes for its continued
29 success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Buc-ee's, the public, and the press.
